      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOOKIN' SUAVE HARV (1) finished off strongly on debut at Moruya, closing well from the back of the pack to only be 0.8L off the winner. Out to 1200m is a big tick for him and he should be able to take closer order. Handled the soggy conditions there and can notch up his maiden win. RED ROCQUETTE (9) trialled well coming into her debut and was well backed, jumping an odds-on pop when beaten 0.4L. Collett rides now from an inside barrier and she showed on debut that the wet deck is no issue. Can make her presence felt again. LADY GOT BLING (5) can resume on a positive note with the benefit of race experience under her belt. NIKITA ZOU (8) was no match behind Golden Slipper placegetter Music Time on debut. Expecting a better performance on resumption.",
